data.title: Led Zeppelin Led Zeppelin IV - 4th - Overstickered Label - Crossed out B UK Vinyl LP
data.meta_description: LED ZEPPELIN Led Zeppelin IV (1971 UK fourth issue 8-track vinyl LP on the plum & red label with the printing errors corrected by the careful placement of two stickers, returning the 'LED ZEPPELIN' name to the top of the label & over stickering the 'Executive Producer: Peter Grant' credit that Jimmy Page didn't approve of & with 'Kinney Music Ltd./Superhype publishing' credits. This copy has A/3 & B/4 matrices with the crossed out B at the end of the A Side Matrix, housed in a gate Tracklisting & Info: Condition The sleeve has a few spots of discolouration with no splits or tears. The inner has the external flipback and has a seam split to the bottom & one side with a crease from manufacturing. The labels are clean with little sign of spindle wear. The vinyl has light scuffs to Side One, which whilst noticeable does not impact the play, leaving it VG/EX A fantastic copy of this national treasure! Tracklisting Side A 1. Black Dog 2. Rock & Roll 3. The Battle Of Evermore 4. Stairway To Heaven Side B 1. Misty Mountain Hop 2. Four Sticks 3. Going To California 4. When The Levee Breaks Year of Release - 1971 Format - vinyl LP album (LP record) Record Label - Atlantic Catalogue No - 2401012 Country of Origin - United Kingdom

LED ZEPPELIN Led Zeppelin IV (1971 UK fourth issue 8-track vinyl LP on the plum & red label with the printing errors corrected by the careful placement of two stickers, returning the 'LED ZEPPELIN' name to the top of the label & over stickering the 'Executive Producer: Peter Grant' credit that Jimmy Page didn't approve of & with 'Kinney Music Ltd./Superhype publishing' credits. This copy has A/3 & B/4 matrices with the crossed out B at the end of the A Side Matrix, housed in a gatefold picture sleeve with extrnal flipback style lyric inner)

Condition

The sleeve has a few spots of discolouration with no splits or tears.

The inner has the external flipback and has a seam split to the bottom & one side with a crease from manufacturing.

The labels are clean with little sign of spindle wear. The vinyl has light scuffs to Side One, which whilst noticeable does not impact the play, leaving it VG/EX
